Message.Title: Romney's tax plan crunches middle class
Message.Msg: According to the Tax Policy Center analysis, Romney's plan to extend the Bush tax cuts for everyone, lower marginal tax rates by 20 percent, eliminate the alternative minimum tax and estate taxes and get rid of taxes on investment income for most taxpayers, while not adding to the deficit, would be a boon for top earners alone. People making $1 million or more would see an average tax cut of $87,000. But people making under $200,000 would see their taxes go up. Those earning between $75,000 and $100,000 per year would see their taxes increase $884. http://www.tampabay.com/opinion/editorials/article1244067.ece
